<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="844" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.62/17a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d844fn1">See also telegram of Feb. 3 (No. 3860) to the
                                    Ambassador in Germany, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_585">p. 585</ref>.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-03T13:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>209. German Ambassador here, together with his staff, will be handed
                                passport at 2 p.m. to-day. Immediately inform Spanish Government of
                                this Government’s desire that American interests in Germany may be
                                cared for by the Spanish Embassy at Berlin and request instructions
                                be telegraphed there immediately.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>